Privacy Policy

Last updated: 26 September 2026

This Privacy Policy describes how information is handled when you use Delayed (the “App”).

By using the App, you agree to this Privacy Policy.

1. Information Collection
Personal Information

The App does not collect, store, or require any personal information such as name, email address, phone number, or physical address.

The App does not require account registration.

Automatically Collected Information

Some information may be collected automatically by third-party services used in the App, including:

Device information (such as device model and operating system)

Advertising identifiers (such as Google Advertising ID)

App interaction data related to ads and app stability

This information is used only to provide advertisements, process purchases, and improve app performance.

2. Advertising

The App uses Google AdMob to display advertisements.

AdMob may collect and use information such as:

Advertising identifiers

Device information

Approximate location (non-precise)

Advertisements are shown only at natural breaks in gameplay and never during active play.

Users may permanently remove all ads through a one-time in-app purchase.

For more information about how Google handles data, please visit:
https://policies.google.com/privacy

3. In-App Purchases

The App offers a one-time in-app purchase to remove advertisements permanently.

All purchases are processed securely through Google Play Billing.
The App does not collect or store any payment or financial information.

Purchase status may be checked locally on the device to restore purchases after reinstalling the App.

4. Data Storage

The App stores limited data locally on your device only, such as:

Game progress

App settings (including ads removal status)

No game data is transmitted to external servers.

5. Third-Party Services

The App uses the following third-party services:

Google AdMob (advertising)

Google Play Billing (in-app purchases)

These services operate under their own privacy policies.

6. Children’s Privacy

The App does not knowingly collect personal information from children under the age of 13.

7. Changes to This Privacy Policy

This Privacy Policy may be updated from time to time.
Any updates will be posted with a revised “Last updated” date.

8. Contact

If you have questions about this Privacy Policy, you may contact the developer through the App’s Google Play Store listing.
